If you are looking for a Kosher place, you may consider this steakhouse. I had a business meeting with a coworker, and since he is Jewish, he asked to meet at Mabat. The food was delicious: from the salads to the bread and of course the meet. The place is not so big (when is said steak house i expected a huge place), but it is clean and the people are very nice. I think they are a little over priced, but my friend told me that the Jewish Kosher places are usually more expensive. Good food.

I've been coming to Mabat for 25 Years. Their Steaks are the Finest Meats & the Best, Always cooked to Perfection! I love this Place & if you're a Vegetarian, they have over 15 Salads for everyones tastes. Mabat's Rib Steaks are my Favorite & check out the Large Sineya(Beef, Chicken, Turkey, Onions & Mushrooms)Awesome(Gevaldic)! All Steaks come with Grilled Onions & Fresh, Hot Pitas Oh and don't Forget the Chicken Soup with Matzo Balls or for a Middle Eastern Taste...The Yeminite Soup! Mabat is a Cozy Place on the Side Street Between Quentin Road & Kings Highway, Check it out...You'll be Glad you did!!!
